%I A396551 #10 May 31 2026 09:45:25
%S A396551 144,576,1568,123008,8258048,9007061816311808
%N A396551 Powerful numbers that are equal to the sum of their coreful divisors that are not exponential unitary divisors.
%C A396551 See A284318 and A361255 for the definitions of coreful divisors and exponential unitary divisors, respectively.
%C A396551 a(7) > 10^18.
%C A396551 If p is a Mersenne prime exponent (A000043) such that p+2 is prime power (A246655), then 2^(p+2) * (2^p-1)^2 is a term.
%C A396551 Of the 52 known Mersenne prime exponents, only 7 have this property: 2, 3, 5, 7, 17, 107 and 521.
%C A396551 a(1) and a(3)-a(6) are of this form, corresponding to p = 2, 3, 5, 7 and 17. The next terms of this form are 2^109 * (2^107 - 1)^2 = 1.708...*10^97 and 2^523 * (2^521 - 1)^2 = 1.294*10^471.
%C A396551 If m is a term and k is a squarefree number coprime to m, then k*m is a term of A396550. Therefore, A396550 can be generated from this sequence by multiplying with coprime squarefree numbers, and the asymptotic density of A396550can be calculated from this sequence (see comment in A396550).
%t A396551 f1[p_, e_] = (p^(e+1)-1)/(p-1) - 1;
%t A396551 f2[p_, e_] = DivisorSum[e, p^# &, CoprimeQ[#, e/#] &];
%t A396551 q[k_] := Module[{fct = FactorInteger[k]}, Min[fct[[;;, 2]]] > 1 && Times @@ f1 @@@ fct - Times @@ f2 @@@ fct == k]; q[1] = False; Select[Range[150000], q]
%o A396551 (PARI) isok(k) = {my(f = factor(k)); ispowerful(f) && prod(i = 1, #f~, (f[i,1]^(f[i,2]+1) - 1)/(f[i,1]-1) - 1) - prod(i = 1, #f~, sumdiv(f[i,2], d, if(gcd(d, f[i,2]/d) == 1, f[i,1]^d))) == k;}
%Y A396551 Intersection of A001694 and A396550.
%Y A396551 Cf. A000043, A005117, A246655, A284318, A307959, A361255, A391281, A396546, A396549.
%K A396551 nonn,more,new
%O A396551 1,1
%A A396551 _Amiram Eldar_, May 29 2026
